{
  "text": "Targeted therapies have evolved in medicine following advances in molecular technology and the successful mapping of the human genome. Such treatments are well recognized in oncology, where molecules required for tumor growth and spread are specifically targeted to stop the malignant process or prevent tumor progression [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
